item.title: GSK Raises Profit Guidance
item.description: GSK said it now expects adjusted operating profit to increase between 13-15% after it reported a rise in net profit in the third quarter, mainly due to the U.S. launch of its Arexvy vaccine.

item.title: Bond Investors Seen Yearning for Year-End Recovery
item.description: Bond investors are hoping for a year-end recovery, Commerzbank Research said, “as sentiment remains shaky, hopes among bond investors are running high that a dreadful September/October will give way to a positive year-end performance, similar to last year.”

item.title: Orsted Books Impairments, Walks Away From U.S. Offshore Projects
item.description: Orsted booked a $4 billion impairment charge in the third quarter related to its U.S. offshore wind portfolio and said it will stop development of two wind farm projects off the coast of New Jersey amid spiraling costs and supplier delays.

item.title: Nikkei Rises 2.4%, Driven by Strong Earnings Results
item.description: Japanese stocks ended broadly higher, led by companies posting strong results, as concerns eased for now about the Middle East conflict and costs of energy.

item.title: BHP CEO Says China Commodity Demand Robust Despite Economic Struggles
item.description: China’s demand for commodities including iron ore and copper remains robust, the chief executive of mining giant BHP Group said, even as the country’s economic recovery disappoints and its property sector struggles.

item.title: Toyota Motor Nearly Tripled Second-Quarter Profit
item.description: Toyota Motor raised its full-year earnings guidance after saying second-quarter net profit nearly tripled from a year earlier, as sales grew thanks to an easing chip shortage.

item.title: USD/SGD Consolidates Ahead of FOMC Decision
item.description: USD/SGD consolidated in the afternoon Asian session ahead of the FOMC decision due out later in the global day.

item.title: Israeli Airstrike Hits Crowded Refugee Camp in Northern Gaza
item.description: The Israeli military said it hit a Hamas command and tunnel network in northern Gaza, causing widespread casualties and damage in a crowded Palestinian refugee camp.

item.title: China's Property Developers Cut Prices---and Homeowners Are Resisting
item.description: Local governments are grappling with the challenge of allowing home prices to fall.

item.title: U.S. All but Stopped Spying on Hamas in Years After 9/11
item.description: The CIA outsourced intelligence gathering on Palestinian groups to Israel after the Sept. 11, 2001, attacks, focusing instead on the hunt for al Qaeda and Islamic State leaders.

item.title: After a Boom and Bust, Chip Industry Is Regaining Its Health
item.description: Intel, Samsung and others see a semiconductor rebound as tech demand starts to recover.

item.title: The Death Rate for Babies in America Rose for the First Time in 20 Years
item.description: The rate of babies dying in the U.S. increased 3% from 2021 to 2022, the CDC says.
